2025-11-28T16:33:18.5618232Z copilot: Now I understand the issue! The workflow runs `npx playwright test` which by default looks for `playwright.config.js` (or `playwright.config.ts`), which uses `defineConfig`. 
2025-11-28T16:33:18.5619358Z 
2025-11-28T16:33:18.5620958Z The main `playwright.config.js` file uses the new API (`defineConfig`), but there's an issue with the ESM module resolution. This is likely related to the `type: "module"` in `package.json`.
2025-11-28T16:33:18.5622016Z 
2025-11-28T16:33:18.5623096Z Looking at this more carefully, the issue is that the Playwright CLI uses its own ESM loader mechanism that might be conflicting with how the config file is loaded.
2025-11-28T16:33:18.5624038Z 
2025-11-28T16:33:18.5624957Z Let me fix this by modifying `playwright.config.js` to not use `defineConfig` (similar to how `playwright.config.firefox.js` is done):

2025-11-28T16:40:20.5793889Z     139.             resolve(false);
2025-11-28T16:40:20.5794251Z     140.           }

2025-11-28T16:40:38.9302322Z     54. export async function waitForExtensionLoad(page, timeout = 5000) {
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9303419Z     55.   // Wait for content script to inject by checking for extension-specific elements
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9304196Z     56.   await page
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9305151Z     57.     .waitForFunction(
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9305575Z     58.       () => {

2025-11-28T16:40:38.9307074Z     60.         return (
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9307714Z     61.           window.quickTabsManager !== undefined ||
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9308230Z     62.           document.querySelector('[data-quick-tab-id]') !== null ||

2025-11-28T16:40:38.9309298Z     64.         ); // Extension may not inject anything immediately
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9309726Z     65.       },
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9310050Z     66.       { timeout }
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9310369Z     67.     )
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9310856Z     68.     .catch(() => {
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9311477Z     69.       // Extension may not inject anything on initial load - this is okay
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9312108Z     70.       console.log('Extension load check timed out (expected if no Quick Tabs exist)');
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9312661Z     71.     });
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9316465Z     72. }
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9316909Z     73. 
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9317223Z     74. /**
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9317613Z     75.  * Clears all extension storage
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9318077Z     76.  *

2025-11-28T16:40:38.9319187Z     78.  */
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9319699Z     79. export async function clearExtensionStorage(page) {
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9320340Z     80.   await page.evaluate(async () => {
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9321102Z     81.     if (typeof browser !== 'undefined') {
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9322008Z     82.       await browser.storage.sync.clear();
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9322639Z     83.       await browser.storage.local.clear();
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9323241Z     84.       if (browser.storage.session) {
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9323907Z     85.         await browser.storage.session.clear();
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9324576Z     86.       }
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9324994Z     87.     }
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9325389Z     88.   });
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9325790Z     89. }
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9326125Z     90. 
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9326511Z     91. /**

2025-11-28T16:40:38.9328386Z     94.  * @param {Page} page - The page to execute storage get on

2025-11-28T16:40:38.9330897Z     97.  */
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9331554Z     98. export async function getExtensionStorage(page, key = null) {
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9332349Z     99.   return page.evaluate(async storageKey => {
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9333050Z     100.     if (typeof browser !== 'undefined') {
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9333844Z     101.       const syncData = await browser.storage.sync.get(storageKey);
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9334759Z     102.       const localData = await browser.storage.local.get(storageKey);
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9335583Z     103.       return { sync: syncData, local: localData };
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9336158Z     104.     }
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9336648Z     105.     return { sync: {}, local: {} };
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9337162Z     106.   }, key);
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9337633Z     107. }
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9338027Z     108.

2025-11-28T16:40:38.9339107Z     111.  *
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9339436Z     112.  * @param {Page} page - The page to trigger shortcut on

2025-11-28T16:40:38.9340422Z     114.  */
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9341141Z     115. export async function triggerShortcut(page, shortcut) {
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9341799Z     116.   const keys = shortcut.split('+');
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9342505Z     117.   const modifiers = keys.slice(0, -1);
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9343086Z     118.   const key = keys[keys.length - 1];
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9346718Z     119. 
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9348416Z     120.   // Press modifiers
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9348850Z     121.   for (const modifier of modifiers) {
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9349281Z     122.     await page.keyboard.down(modifier);
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9349623Z     123.   }
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9349943Z     124. 
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9350161Z     125.   // Press main key
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9350664Z     126.   await page.keyboard.press(key);
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9351012Z     127. 
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9351245Z     128.   // Release modifiers
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9351726Z     129.   for (const modifier of modifiers.reverse()) {
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9352108Z     130.     await page.keyboard.up(modifier);
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9352519Z     131.   }
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9352726Z     132. }
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9352923Z     133. 
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9353244Z     134. /**

2025-11-28T16:40:38.9355149Z     139.  * @returns {Promise<ElementHandle>} The Quick Tab element
2025-11-28T16:40:38.9355479Z     140.  */

2025-11-28T16:45:10.7768287Z     const keys = shortcut.split('+');
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7768518Z     const modifiers = keys.slice(0, -1);
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7768741Z     const key = keys[keys.length - 1];
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7768880Z   
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7769036Z     // Press modifiers
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7769267Z     for (const modifier of modifiers) {
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7769505Z       await page.keyboard.down(modifier);
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7769648Z     }
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7769786Z   
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7769953Z     // Press main key
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7770174Z     await page.keyboard.press(key);
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7770399Z   
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7770709Z     // Release modifiers
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7770979Z     for (const modifier of modifiers.reverse()) {
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7771298Z       await page.keyboard.up(modifier);
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7771443Z     }
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7771583Z   }

2025-11-28T16:45:10.7817378Z       // Set up message listener to capture the toggle action
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7817652Z       const messagePromise = page.evaluate(() => {
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7817880Z         return new Promise(resolve => {
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7818102Z           let toggleReceived = false;
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7818240Z   
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7818438Z           // Intercept messages
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7818764Z           browser.runtime.onMessage.addListener(message => {
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7819078Z             if (message.action === 'TOGGLE_QUICK_TABS_PANEL') {
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7819295Z               toggleReceived = true;
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7819464Z               resolve(true);
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7819620Z             }
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7819768Z           });
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7819906Z   
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7820114Z           // Timeout after 5 seconds
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7820289Z           setTimeout(() => {
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7820667Z             if (!toggleReceived) {
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7820841Z               resolve(false);
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7820982Z             }
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7821133Z           }, 5000);
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7821279Z         });
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7821423Z       });
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7821562Z   
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7821767Z       // Trigger keyboard shortcut
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7822044Z       await triggerShortcut(page, 'Control+Alt+Z');
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7822187Z   
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7822410Z       // Wait for message to be received
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7822681Z       const toggleReceived = await messagePromise;
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7822816Z   
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7823041Z       expect(toggleReceived).toBe(true);
2025-11-28T16:45:10.7823188Z     });

2025-11-28T16:45:27.0528182Z       
2025-11-28T16:45:27.0528379Z       ## Root Cause
2025-11-28T16:45:27.0528660Z       The issue was caused by a combination of:
2025-11-28T16:45:27.0529281Z       1. ESM module resolution issues with named exports from `@playwright/test` when using the Playwright CLI's custom ESM loader
2025-11-28T16:45:27.0530216Z       2. Version conflict between `@playwright/mcp` (which depended on `playwright@1.57.0-alpha`) and `@playwright/test` (which depends on `playwright@1.57.0`)
2025-11-28T16:45:27.0531153Z

2025-11-28T16:48:00.9056973Z copilot: The fix is complete. Let me provide a summary of what was done:
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9057370Z 
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9057493Z ## Summary
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9057639Z 
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9058684Z I fixed the Playwright E2E test failure caused by the SyntaxError: "The requested module '@playwright/test' does not provide an export named 'defineConfig'".
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9059998Z 
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9060233Z ### Root Cause
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9061034Z The issue was caused by a combination of:
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9063227Z 1. **ESM module resolution conflict**: The Playwright CLI uses a custom ESM loader that had issues resolving named exports from `@playwright/test` when there were version conflicts
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9066641Z 2. **Version conflict**: The `@playwright/mcp` package depended on `playwright@1.57.0-alpha-2025-11-14` while `@playwright/test` depended on `playwright@1.57.0` stable, causing module resolution to fail
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9067686Z 
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9067829Z ### Changes Made
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9068007Z 
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9068183Z 1. **playwright.config.js**: 
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9068948Z    - Removed `defineConfig` and `devices` imports from `@playwright/test`
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9070361Z    - Changed to use a plain object export (consistent with the working `playwright.config.firefox.js`)
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9071344Z 
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9071591Z 2. **package.json**:
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9072396Z    - Added npm `overrides` for `playwright` and `playwright-core` to force version `1.57.0`
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9073538Z    - Moved `@playwright/mcp` from `dependencies` to `devDependencies` (it's a dev tool, not a runtime dependency)
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9074189Z    - Added `tslib` as a `devDependency` (required by `playwright-webextext`)
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9074477Z 
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9074750Z 3. **Test files** (changed from named imports to default import pattern):
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9075897Z    - `tests/e2e/fixtures/extension.js`: Changed `import { test, firefox } from '@playwright/test'` to `import playwright from 'playwright/test'` and destructure
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9076642Z    - `tests/e2e/helpers/extension-loader.js`: Same pattern change
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9077352Z    - `tests/e2e/v1.6.0-critical-fixes.spec.js`: Same pattern change
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9077939Z 
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9078046Z ### Verification
2025-11-28T16:48:00.9078527Z - `npx playwright test --list` now successfully lists 20 tests
